pageContext.claim: “Remember they were going to win the Senate, but I campaigned I made 32 major stops in a short period of time. Do you think that's easy? And then I had to make two more on the final day of a runoff. Cindy Hyde-Smith, she won, she did great, she did great, but that was -- that was a lot of work and we won the Senate, we got no praise, we got no acclaim, we got nothing.”
pageContext.analysis: There was extensive coverage of the Senate races. There is little historic about a one-seat gain in the Senate; Republicans had started the session with 52 seats. In fact, given that mostly Democratic seats were up for reelection, in many red seats, the outcome was not unexpected.
